    "5. What percentage of revenue does the model attribute to media vs. baseline? Compare to the true value (55% baseline) — how close did the model get?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 7: Experiments — Change a Prior\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the core learning section. You'll change one prior, refit the model, and compare results to the original."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Experiment A: Tighten the ROI prior to be more skeptical of high ROI\n",
    "# Original: HalfNormal(scale=1.0)\n",
    "# New: HalfNormal(scale=0.5) — stronger belief that ROI < 1.5x\n",
    "\n",
    "roi_prior_tight = tfd.HalfNormal(scale=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "model_spec_tight = model_spec.ModelSpec(\n",
    "    roi_prior=roi_prior_tight,\n",
    "    adstock_prior=adstock_prior,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "mmm_tight = Meridian(\n",
    "    input_data=input_data,\n",
    "    model_spec=model_spec_tight,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Fitting model with tighter ROI prior...')\n",
    "mmm_tight.fit(\n",
    "    num_chains=4,\n",
    "    num_samples=500,\n",
    "    num_warmup=500,\n",
    "    seed=42,\n",
    ")\n",
    "print('Done.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compare ROI estimates: original vs. tight prior\n",
    "roi_original = mmm.get_roi_summary(confidence_level=0.90)\n",
    "roi_tight    = mmm_tight.get_roi_summary(confidence_level=0.90)\n",
    "\n",
    "comparison = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'channel':          ['TV', 'Search', 'Social', 'Display'],\n",
    "    'roi_original':     roi_original['roi_median'].values,\n",
    "    'roi_tight_prior':  roi_tight['roi_median'].values,\n",
    "    'true_roi':         [2.1, 4.3, 2.8, 1.4],\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "print('ROI Comparison:')\n",
    "print(comparison.round(3))"
   ]
